  "text": "From thereafter, the search for the \"clock\" started. In 1971, Konopka and Benzer identified the first clock gene-Period-in Drosophila melanogaster by an EMS-induced mutant screen [CITATION_1] . The following milestone in circadian rhythms research was the identification of the suprachiasmatic nucleus (SCN)-a brain region located in the hypothalamus-as the central pacemaker of the circadian clock, in 1990 [CITATION_2] .",
